    Reextracted Peak Intensity Set

    reextracted_compound_intensities.Rd

    Produce a table of reextracted peak intensities based on a short list of curated peak groups

    reextracted_compound_intensities(
  curated_mzrolldb,
  full_mzrolldb,
  sample_folder,
  min_mz_delta = 0.01,
  min_rt_delta = 0.1,
  verbose = TRUE,
  debug = FALSE
)

    Arguments

    curated_mzrolldb

    mzrollDB file containing manually verified peakgroups. peaks and peakgroups from this table are used in this method.

    full_mzrolldb

    mzrollDB file containing original rt_update_key RT alignment table. This table is used for transforming sample_rt <--> aligned_rt

    sample_folder

    folder containing all raw samples to apply reextraction.

    min_mz_delta

    adjust min and max m/z so that the difference is at least this value.

    min_rt_delta

    adjust min and max rt so that the difference is at least this value.

    verbose

    flag for explicit printing

    debug

    flag for debugging

    Value

    intensities_table Each row indicates quant values for a single peak (an annotated feature in a single sample.) Both aligned RT coordinates and sample RT coordinates are given.

    sample:

    sample name

    sampleId:

    ID number for sample in mzrolldb files

    groupId:

    group ID number from curated_mzrolldb file

    compoundName:

    String representation of annotated feature

    intensity:

    curated_mzrollDB-recorded intensity (peakAreaTop), or reextracted intensity

    is_identified:

    if TRUE, using quant from curated_mzrolldb. Else, reextract from sample file

    mzmin:

    minimum m/z associated with peak

    mzmax:

    maximum m/z associated with peak

    aligned_rtmin:

    minimum RT value associated with peak, in aligned RT space. Relies on rt_update_key table in full_mzrolldb

    aligned_rtmax:

    maximum RT value associated with peak, in aligned RT space. Relies on rt_update_key table in full_mzrolldb

    sample_rtmin:

    minimum RT value associated with peak, in mzML/mzXML sample space.

    sample_rtmax:

    maximum RT value associated with peak, in mzML/mzXML sample space.
